"metaSummary_en": "Mega Altaria ex Espeon is still by far the most played deck (7.53% usage) but caps at 50.48% win rate; the best genuinely playable win rate belongs to Mega Manectric ex Zeraora (52.15%, 2% usage), just ahead of Suicune ex Baxcalibur (51.86%), Mega Altaria ex Gourgeist (51.58%) and Mega Blaziken ex Greninja (51.48%). The meta stays very stable in the wake of Everyday Wonders and remains dominated by Mega decks and Magnezone/Miraidon variants; only a few seat swaps shake up the top 10 (Mega Blaziken and Zoroark ex rise, Magnezone Miraidon ex and Mega Altaria ex Gourgeist each drop a rank). High-win-rate outsiders to watch: Mega Altaria ex Greninja (52.92%, best win rate of the format), Jolteon ex Jolteon (52.83%), Iron Valiant Iron Boulder (52.67%), Mega Lucario ex (52.02%) and Sylveon ex Mega Altaria ex (51.57%, boosted by the new set). Hot news: the Everyday Wonders mini-expansion (B3b) has been live since June 29 (6:00 p.m. PDT, June 30 in Asia), led by Mega Diancie ex alongside Pikachu, Piplup, Snorlax, Greedent and Sylveon. July brings the Everyday Wonders Emblem Event, Community Week, a Growlithe/Emolga wonder pick and the Hisuian Zorua Drop Event, before the major Ruler of the Skies expansion (B4, ~July 30, Mega Rayquaza ex).",
